texts.text: Child. I ask again.
Do you wish to keep living your life as you have until now?
If so, then lend me your strength.
This poison will consume this world and bring the end for all.
I want to save everyone.
They're complete strangers, but they saved me when I was in trouble...
I don't want to forget that feeling.
When I made my decision back there, I felt a lot better about myself.
I can't deny that I've been ignorant when it came to other people.
But I want to be more open and not so closed off.
I want to save them because I feel like I can now...
And work towards being a better person.
*Wince*
Can anyone hear me? I hope none of you have gotten hurt.
This air feels awful and I'm getting worried. I hope you're all still okay.
Hey! Where y'all at?! Say somethin' if you can hear me!

*Cough*
I can't... Breathe... My throat...

*Cough*
C'mon! Someone say somethin'!
We're all getting out of here. I'll do whatever I can to make it happen...!
Everyone's voices...? Where? Are they close?
The other voices that I heard coming from the poison are starting to fade...
Their voices are overpowering the other ones?
These... These voices... These thoughts...
>The demon wrapped in poison starts to emit some kind of light!
Wait, what...?!
I have sensed the pride and sorrow these humans feel for this land.
Your strength lies in "actions".
In turn, we will be able to harness that energy and protect this land.
*Roar*
>A demon covered in dragon scales rises to the air and descends back down.
>The wind swirls into a tornado and begins sweeping away the poison.
The poisons starting to dissipate...
...?! Wait, that looks like...!
*Groan*
Everyone, please wake up!
*Wince*
[sys user_name]! Can you hear me?!
Calm down.
We switched spots.
You should be more anxious...
But I'm so glad you're okay.
We switched spots?
Oh, when I almost fell off that cliff...
Wait, no...! Don't pull my leg like that! But I guess that means you're okay!
Are you the source of those voices?
Fear not. Your eyes are open now. And I have no intention of fighting you.
Our eyes are open?
You are the ones that were calling forth this evil.
Deep underground was where the closed off minds of you humans dwelled.
A massive swell of evil
that was strong enough to be able to drain even my powers.
Turning a blind eye towards others, and yourself for that matter,
let this evil fester and sap the pride and respect that others may have had.
It nearly brought this land to ruin.
There were few visible signs, but this peaceful land was headed towards that.
Nearly to ruin...
You are the one that dared face me. What is your name?
Me?! Uh, it's Kasuga...
Kasuga...

*Chuckle*
I shall remember thy name, Kasuga.
Now, to clean up this mess.
Come, ye who took charge and protected this land!
>The demon conjures up another tornado.
>And he begins to rise to the air!
Come... Wait, hang on?!
Hang on! No way!
Trust him.
Be brave.
Screw it, let's just go for it!
Let's go on three! One! Two! Three!
>You and everyone else dive into the swirling vortex!
Wait! There's... Something's happening down below.
And something's coming this way...?
Boss, another bad one and we might be done for!
Yo, just get ready!
This is... Take-Minakata?
Yes. I sense his presence.
Well, I suppose the time to decide his punishment has finally arrived!
>A powerful gust of wind rises as it slices the demons in its path!
*Roar*
*Groan*
There. We have finally returned to the surface.
And they are here as well...
*Scream*
W-we're falling!!
Oh my! Devil Download!
>Seiran summons a demon that breaks everyone's fall...
Welcome back, Newbie! Successful as always, I see?
Great job, Newbie! You did overdo it a bit though...
Yo, and that demon's...
You... You are Take-Minakata, but with the powers of a dragon after being consumed by that poison.
No, I am no longer Take-Minakata.
I acquired this power by becoming the defender of this land, Koga Saburo.
As long as people feel pride and sorrow for this land, I will not fail. Not ever.
Not ever...?
So that means you can do something about...?
>The serpents climb their way out of the chasm and begin their assault...!
Ah, the collateral damage I have caused...
For the sake of this land... I shall vanquish each and every one of these demons.
>Koga Saburo readies his sword and eyes the serpents.
The sorrow felt for this land... The one true defender of these borders...
The Dragon, Koga Saburo.
For the sake of this land, I must prevail.
*Strike*
Yo, we're fightin' too! It's the final battle!
I believe that is the last of them...
I apologize for the troubles I may have caused, Susano-o. And Kushinada.
Oh, you have no idea!
Susano-o was about to bury you alive before I stepped in.
That is a path we must consider if this were to happen again.
We simply wish to hear that you are grateful!
Yo, we cleaned everythin' up so fast!
Hard to believe we were havin' so much trouble before...
Now, humans.
Be it humans or demons,
I have no mercy on those who bargain away their pride and sorrow.
Which is why you must never forget the pride and sorrow you feel now.
That might be easier said than done...
I wonder if we really can keep feeling that way about day to day...
What we can do as individuals really isn't all that much.
True.
Which is why we need to do everything we can collectively.
I don't really know what it means to feel that kind of "sorrow",
but closing myself off and avoiding anything that might be bothersome...
I feel like I can at least work towards not doing that.
I think...
Yeah... It might even lead to having some actual pride.
Yo, takin' your first steps towards that's the most important part.
And not turning a blind eye to others. Looking out for those around you.
Start by lending them a hand when you can.
Just that?
Indeed. Then you will understand what pride and sorrow truly mean.
And you will be able to shape the future of this land.
But we must be off now! Bye bye, everyone!
Farewell...
>The deities leave everyone with their parting words and disappear...
Koga Saburo...
Even after that incident... It still feels like it was all a dream.
I decided to join a group that consults people about bullying.
Even if that was all a dream,
I was still able to change how I feel and learned how to take action.
It's a complicated issue with a lot of trouble waiting up ahead,
but I feel better about myself for doing this.
And that's it for the people that fell into that Aura Gate...
I was worried for a little bit but they all seem fine in the end.
Especially Kasuga. She's really changed since then.
She looks much better than before.
The way Newbie told me, you'd think she was a different person.
Is this about that giant hole?
Based on what I've heard, their situation had to be the reason behind what they did.
When humans sense any danger, we're supposedly hardwired to work together
in order to increase our chances of survival.
That's so cut and dry...
You always try to wrap everything into a tidy little package.
I'm just being objective. You're just too emotional for your own good.
But Shiori may be onto something.
Everyone sensed danger and thought through about what they needed to do,
and worked together in the end to find a solution.
But there's really no point if danger is what ultimately triggers that.
What about lending a helping hand when someone's in trouble?
Or rather making it a part of your daily routine to help out others.
What are you, a bunch of wannabe saints?
I'm all about "quid pro quo".
Give and take when it suits your needs. It's worked out for me so far.
Honey agrees!
Get what you need and toss the rest! Just like a villain!
Like a villain? That's what villains do...
Everyone lends a helpin' hand when they can.
Yo, if everyone connects with people like that
malice and ignorance might disappear altogether.
I want y'all to think about that from now on.
Yeah, of course. It's important to help others out.
Which is why it'd be great if everyone helped with this...♡
>Ririn gets out a pile of paper for origami.
What's this...?
I'm making a costume to match the one Himika's going to wear
and my character's outfit has an origami crane theme.
Which is why I need a thousand cranes strung together for it to work.
Uh, I have some work to do for school.
I need to get started on my homework too.
I need to eat chips or else I'll die.
My fingers are gonna be all oily, so I can't really help.
No way. It's your problem, not mine.
Hey, wait!
If everyone helps, then it's that much less work to do!
Hello?! What happened to helping each other out...!!
